{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 08:16:25.363115", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and topology\\n- Fabric: 3-tier EBGP Clos with super-spine (AS65000) to spines (AS65100/65101), spines to leaves (AS65200/65201), leaves advertising 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24.\\n- Hosts: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 via leaf_router_0_0), pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 via leaf_router_0_1).\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- Control plane (BGP) across the fabric is up and correctly distributing the two /24 leaf prefixes.\\n- Data plane within the fabric is healthy (spine-to-leaf SVI reachability OK).\\n- Anomaly: Host pc_0_1 is down/unresponsive on its access subnet. This causes loss of reachability to 10.0.1.2 and any traffic targeting that endpoint. The fabric itself is not the root cause.\\n\\nKey findings and evidence\\n\\n1) BGP health\\n- Leaves established EBGP to spines and learned the remote /24:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0: show ip route includes “C 10.0.0.0/24” and “B 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (eth0)”.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1: show ip route includes “C 10.0.1.0/24” and “B 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (eth0)”.\\n- Spines established EBGP to super-spine and both leaves; both /24s present:\\n  - spine_router_0_0: “B 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.5; B 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.7”.\\n  - spine_router_0_1: “B 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.9; B 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.11”.\\n- Super-spine has both /24s via spine links.\\n- Note: Minor inconsistency observed in BGP summaries: spine_router_0_0 shows 0 prefixes received from super-spine while spine_router_0_1 shows 2. No impact observed because spines learn leaf routes directly from leaves.\\n\\n2) Data plane checks\\n- Local host on leaf 0_0 works:\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 can ping 10.0.0.2 (OK).\\n- Host on leaf 0_1 unreachable locally:\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 cannot ping 10.0.1.2 (100% loss).\\n  - ARP on leaf_router_0_1: “10.0.1.2 FAILED” (incomplete neighbor).\\n- Cross-fabric SVI reachability:\\n  - Spines can ping leaf SVIs (e.g., spine_router_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1 OK; spine_router_0_1 -> 10.0.0.1 OK), confirming fabric forwarding is fine.\\n  - Leaf-to-leaf SVI pings (leaf 0_0 -> 10.0.1.1 and leaf 0_1 -> 10.0.0.1) fail. This is expected given infra /31s are not advertised; replies would target 172.16.x addresses without routes on leaves.\\n- Host state via tools:\\n  - Attempts to run commands against pc_0_1 repeatedly failed with “container ... is not running”.\\n  - get_host_net_config succeeded for pc_0_0 but not for pc_0_1.\\n\\nAnomalies detected\\n- pc_0_1 is not running/unreachable at L2/L3 on its access network:\\n  - ARP failure on leaf_router_0_1 (eth2).\\n  - Ping from directly-connected leaf to 10.0.1.2 fails.\\n  - Tooling indicates pc_0_1 container not running.\\n- Minor control-plane asymmetry: spine_router_0_0 does not show received prefixes from super-spine while spine_router_0_1 does; no functional impact observed.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_1 (host behind leaf_router_0_1).\\n- Fabric devices (leaves/spines/super-spine) show healthy links and BGP sessions; routes installed as expected.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- The end-host pc_0_1 is down (container not running), resulting in ARP resolution failure on leaf_router_0_1 and loss of reachability to 10.0.1.2. The data-center fabric control and forwarding planes are operating normally., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='2c71702c-453f-45f8-99d8-3864e27632f4'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
